title: Jar And Cover, ca. 1810
description: Round body cut with vertical flutes in graduated lengths, prismatic cutting above and below, with vertical flutes around lip, a star on bottom of base; domed cover with mushroom finial cut with star, sies cut with blazes of graduated lengths and short row vertical flutes at outer rim.

tombstone.epitaph:
Jar And Cover, ca. 1810.
ca. 1810. glass. Bequest of Walter Phelps Warren. 1986-61-153-a,b.
